The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the Sparsest Cut problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the form of embeddings and low-dimensional approximations. The paper also discusses spectral graph theory (cs.SI) and its application to the integrality gap of the Goemans-Linial SDP relaxation. Finally, the paper involves computational geometry (cs.CG) in the form of embedding points into $\ell_1$.
